  "local_port": 41662,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Select Medical?",
  "response": "Starting a new job can be both exciting and nerve-wracking. If you're beginning your first day at **Select Medical**, here are some key things to keep in mind to help you succeed and feel more prepared:\n\n### 1. **Understand the Company Culture**\n   - Select Medical is a healthcare company focused on delivering high-quality patient care and improving outcomes. The culture is likely to be professional, patient-centered, and team-oriented. Be prepared to collaborate and prioritize patient needs.\n\n### 2. **Dress Professionally**\n   - Dress code may vary depending on your role (clinical vs. administrative), but it\u2019s always best to err on the side of professionalism. If unsure, ask your hiring manager or HR contact for guidance.\n\n### 3. **Be Ready to Learn**\n   - The first day often involves onboarding, training, and orientation. Come prepared to take notes, ask questions, and absorb as much information as possible.\n\n### 4. **Familiarize Yourself with Select Medical\u2019s Mission and Values**\n   - Select Medical\u2019s mission is to deliver an exceptional patient experience through specialized healthcare services. Their values likely include compassion, accountability, and excellence. Understanding this will help you align with the company\u2019s goals.\n\n### 5. **Know Your Role and Responsibilities**\n   - Review the job description and be clear on your duties. If you\u2019re unsure about anything, don\u2019t hesitate to ask your supervisor for clarification.\n\n### 6. **Be Punctual**\n   - Arrive early on your first day to make a good impression and allow time for any unexpected delays.\n\n### 7. **Bring Necessary Documents**\n   - Have all required paperwork ready, such as your ID, Social Security card, or other onboarding documents, as requested by HR.\n\n### 8. **Be Open to Networking**\n   - Introduce yourself to colleagues and supervisors. Building relationships early on can help you feel more integrated into the team.\n\n### 9. **Understand the Technology and Tools**\n   - Select Medical may use specific software or systems (e.g., electronic health records). Be prepared to learn and adapt to these tools quickly.\n\n### 10. **Maintain a Positive Attitude**\n   - A positive and willing-to-learn attitude will go a long way. Show enthusiasm and a readiness to contribute to the team.\n\n### 11. **Ask Questions**\n   - Don\u2019t be afraid to ask questions about processes, expectations, or resources. It\u2019s better to clarify early on than to make assumptions.\n\n### 12. **Be Patient with Yourself**\n   - It\u2019s normal to feel overwhelmed on your first day. Give yourself time to adjust and remember that everyone was new once.\n\n### 13. **Know the Policies**\n   - Familiarize yourself with Select Medical\u2019s policies, such as work hours, break times, and communication protocols, to ensure you\u2019re compliant from day one.\n\n### 14. **Show Initiative**\n   - If you see an opportunity to help or contribute, offer your assistance. It demonstrates your commitment and eagerness to be part of the team.\n\n### 15. **Take Care of Yourself**\n   - Starting a new job can be mentally and physically exhausting. Make sure you get enough rest, eat well, and stay hydrated to perform at your best.\n\nBy keeping these tips in mind, you\u2019ll be well-prepared to make a great impression and start your journey with Select Medical on the right foot. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
